# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# zama-indexer environment. For local runs you need NOTHING here: every value below
# has a sensible default, and the token address is read from contracts/deployments.json
# (written by `pnpm local:deploy`).
#
# Create .env.local only to override a default below. Leave a line commented to keep its
# default — setting a var to an EMPTY value replaces the default with nothing and breaks
# startup (defaults apply only when a var is absent, not when it is blank). Never commit a key.
#
# Local-only: Anvil + forge-fhevm; decryption via the SDK's cleartext() transport. The fhEVM
# host addresses (ACL, executor, …) come from the SDK `hardhat` preset and indexing starts at
# block 0 — neither is exposed as a knob, because the local stack is canonical.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# RPC for the local node — used by both Ponder and the SDK. Defaults to http://127.0.0.1:8545.
# PONDER_RPC_URL_31337=http://127.0.0.1:8545

# Holder/delegate EOA — the identity the indexer decrypts as. Defaults to Anvil account #0
# (a public dev key), so leave it commented for local runs; uncomment to index a different
# holder. Use a throwaway test key only — never a real one.
# PRIVATE_KEY=0x...

# ── Ponder / deployment (optional) ───────────────────────────────────────────
# HTTP port the indexer + read API listen on (read by Ponder; the /v1/health self-call
# falls back to it too). Defaults to 42069.
# PORT=42069

# Postgres connection string. Falls back to the embedded SQLite (PGlite) store when unset.
# DATABASE_URL=postgresql://user:pass@localhost:5432/zama_indexer
